headline: Stellantis warns of €2.3 billion first-half loss on tariffs, one-offs
summary: Investing.com -- Stellantis (BIT:STLAM) (NYSE:STLA) expects to post a net loss of €2.3 billion ($2.68 billion) for the first half of 2025, as the automaker faces a range of operational and external pressures, including a €0.3 billion hit from new U.S. import tariffs.
